  <h1>Heelr Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta"><strong>Last updated:</strong> 30 May 2026</p>

  <p>
    Heelr respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the
    Heelr iOS app, including the journal, recovery and mobility tracking features, and the gait scan.
  </p>

  <p>
    Heelr is designed for general consumers who want to log, track, and review their dog&rsquo;s daily activity,
    recovery, and movement over time.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    Heelr is built to collect only what is needed to provide its features. Because Heelr is a journal, some of the
    information you enter is saved so that it is available to you across sessions.
  </p>

  <h3>Dog Profiles and Journal Content</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Information you choose to enter about your dog, such as name, breed, age, weight, and notes.</li>
    <li>Journal entries you create, including text notes, dates, photos, and videos.</li>
    <li>This content is saved so you can view your history, track progress, and review past entries.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Camera and Video (Gait Scans)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>The app allows you to record video using your device camera, or select an existing video, to perform a gait scan and analyse how your dog moves.</li>
    <li>Gait scan video may be processed on your device and/or transmitted to our service providers to generate movement analysis and results.</li>
    <li>By default, your gait scan videos and their results are <strong>saved to your Heelr library</strong> so you can replay scans and compare movement over time. You can delete a scan or its video at any time from within the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Photos</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Photos you capture or select are added to the relevant journal entry or dog profile and saved as part of your content.</li>
    <li>You can delete photos at any time from within the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Health and Mobility Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Heelr stores the recovery, mobility, and gait information you log or that the app generates, such as gait scores, mobility trends, and recovery milestones.</li>
    <li>This relates to your dog and is used to provide tracking, history, and analysis features within the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Location Information</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>If you use activity or walk-tracking features, the app may request access to your device location to record distance or routes at the time you use the feature.</li>
    <li>Location is used to provide that feature and is associated with the relevant journal entry if you choose to save it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Account and Identifiers</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>The app may create an <strong>identifier</strong> to support core functionality such as saving your content, syncing across your devices, managing entitlements, and associating your data with your session.</li>
    <li>If account sign-in is offered, we collect the information needed to create and secure your account.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Usage and Diagnostics Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>The app may collect <strong>anonymous usage events</strong>, such as feature interactions, to support app functionality and basic analytics.</li>
    <li>The app may collect crash reports and performance diagnostics through Apple&rsquo;s built-in tools.</li>
    <li>This information does not identify you personally.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Information We Do Not Collect</h3>
  <p>Heelr does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Advertising identifiers for ad targeting</li>
    <li>Contacts from your device</li>
    <li>Data for tracking you across other apps or websites</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>Information handled by the app is used only to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide core features such as journaling, recovery and mobility tracking, and gait scans</li>
    <li>Generate gait and movement analysis and track changes over time</li>
    <li>Save, sync, and back up your content so it is available to you</li>
    <li>Display and manage subscription access</li>
    <li>Improve app stability and performance</li>
    <li>Understand general feature usage in an anonymous way</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>We do not sell your personal information to advertisers or any third parties, and we do not share your information with advertisers.</strong> We do not use your data for advertising, marketing, or tracking across apps or websites.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Data Storage, Sync, and Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Your journal content, dog profiles, photos, videos, and gait scan results are retained so that the features work and your history is available to you.</li>
    <li>Where sync or backup is enabled, your content may be stored on our service providers&rsquo; infrastructure to make it available across your devices.</li>
    <li>You can delete individual entries, photos, videos, or scans at any time from within the app.</li>
    <li>Location data is used at the time of the request and retained only if you save it to an entry.</li>
    <li>Anonymous usage and diagnostic data may be retained in aggregated form to support app operation and improvements.</li>
    <li>If you delete your account (where accounts are offered), your associated content is deleted, subject to any limited retention required for legal or operational reasons.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>AI and Automated Analysis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Gait scans and certain insights may be generated using automated analysis and/or AI service providers.</li>
    <li>Where processing occurs off-device, the relevant content (such as gait scan video or movement data) may be transmitted to these providers solely to generate your results.</li>
    <li>We use these providers only to deliver app features, not for advertising or cross-app tracking.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>Heelr uses the following third-party services solely to operate the app:</p>

  <h3>Apple Services</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>StoreKit</strong> for In-App Purchases and subscriptions. Payment information is handled entirely by Apple. We do not receive or store payment details.</li>
    <li>Apple&rsquo;s crash and performance diagnostics tools.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cloud Storage and Processing</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>We use cloud infrastructure and processing providers to store your content (where sync or backup is enabled) and to generate gait scan results.</li>
    <li>These providers handle data only to operate the app and do not use it for advertising.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>No third-party services are used for advertising or cross-app tracking.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>We Do Not Sell Your Information</h2>
  <p>
    Heelr does not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to advertisers or any other third parties. We do not
    share your information with advertisers, and we do not allow third parties to use your information for their own
    advertising. The only parties that handle your data are the service providers described above, and they do so solely
    to operate Heelr&rsquo;s features on our behalf.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Your Privacy Rights</h2>
  <p>You control access to device features such as the camera, photo library, and location through iOS system settings.</p>
  <p>You can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Deny or revoke camera, photo library, or location permissions at any time</li>
    <li>View, edit, and delete your journal content, photos, videos, dog profiles, and gait scans within the app</li>
    <li>Request access to or deletion of your data, and (where accounts are offered) delete your account</li>
    <li>Manage or cancel subscriptions through your Apple ID settings</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    To make a privacy request, contact us using the details below.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Children&rsquo;s Privacy</h2>
  <p>Heelr is not directed to children under the age of 13.</p>
  <p>
    The app does not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided
    information through the app, please contact us so we can address the issue.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect changes in the app or legal requirements. Any
    updates will be posted on this page with a revised &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Contact Information</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how Heelr handles privacy, you can contact us at:
  </p>
  <p><a href="mailto:contact@heelr.app">contact@heelr.app</a></p>
